    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="855"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/2564</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Acting Chief of the
                        Division of the American Republics</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                    >Bonsal</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-20">December 20,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I told Señor Vargas Nariño,<note n="21" xml:id="d855fn1">First Secretary of the
                        Colombian Embassy.</note> who called on me in substitution for Ambassador
                    Turbay, who is indisposed, that the Department is continuing its discussion with
                    the Foreign Bondholders Council regarding the Colombian offer of a permanent
                    settlement. I stated that, although <pb facs="0729" n="717" xml:id="pg_717"/> we
                    realized the time factor involved (the first coupon not covered by the current
                    temporary settlement falls due on January 1, 1941), we thought it advisable to
                    make every effort to secure either the approval or at least the neutrality of
                    the Council in regard to the settlement. I said that the Ambassador would be
                    advised immediately we had reached the decision that no further modification of
                    the Council’s attitude could be looked for.</p>
            </div>
